# 4. 抗えない恐怖

Ishihara: Alright, let me give you guys a quick rundown of the rules.
Ishihara: It's actually pretty simple. The thrower will throw the disc, and you get points if your dog catches it...
Ishihara: You have sixty seconds to throw it as many times as you like, and you'll be competing based on how many points you can score.
Honami: I see... So, you want to get in as many throws as possible during that time?
Ishihara: Actually, that's not entirely the case. You can score more points if your dog makes a long-distance catch.
Akito: Which means you can form a strategy based on a lot of short throws or try to maximize the points you score with each throw by going long.
Ishihara: Exactly! Also, you get no points if the disc hits the ground first.
Ishihara: That's why I've been aiming up a little and having Max make catches by jumping.
Akito: Yeah... Now that you mention it, even when I threw his disc in a panic the other day, he jumped up to catch it.
Ishihara: I can show you how high and far Max likes you to throw the disc as we go along.
Akito: Okay.
Ishihara: Anyway, let's start practicing. Once you've gotten the hang of throwing the disc, we'll let Max join in.
Honami: Oh, in that case... Would you like us to keep an eye on Max in the meantime?
Ishihara: That'd be great...! Thank you both very much.
Ishihara: Alright, Shinonome, let's get started!
Akito: Okay.
Akito: (Keep your arm flat while at chest level and...)
Akito: Throw.
Ishihara: Whoa! Nice throw, Shinonome...! Your control's perfect!
Akito: I think I've got the hang of things.
Akito: So, next...
Ishihara: *Nod* I'll go let the others know that we're going to start practicing with Max!
Akito: (Things have been going well so far, but the hard part starts here...)
Akito: (Your dog catching the disc you've thrown isn't the end of it. You have to get it back in order to throw it again.)
Akito: (Getting a disc back from a charging dog...)
Akito: (Now's not the time for that... You've gotta honor the commitment you've made.)
Ishihara: Thanks for waiting, Shinonome! We're back!
Max: Woof!
Akito: Alright, I'll try throwing it...
Ishihara: Okay, let me know if you don't feel comfortable. I'll make sure to stop Max.
Minori: You can do it, Shinonome...!
Akito: (Alright...)
Akito: Max, catch...!
Max: Woof!
Honami: Oh wow... That's incredible, Shinonome. The disc's flying so straight.
Minori: Yeah, and Max is going right after it!
Max: Woof!
Minori: Oh, he jumped up and caught it! That was so cool...!
Ishihara: That just leaves...
Akito: (Now I have to get it back from him and throw it again...)
Max: Pant... Pant... Pant...
Akito: (Keep your cool...)
Max: Pant...! Pant...! Pant...!
Akito: (...! Keep your cool...!)
Little Akito: N-Nooooo...!
Akito: ...!
Ishihara: Uh-oh...! Max, stop!
Max: Woof!
Ishihara: Alright, good boy. Come here.
Akito: Damn...
Minori: Oh...
Honami: Are you okay, Shinonome...?
Akito: Yeah...
Akito: (What am I doing...?)
Ishihara: I'm sorry, Shinonome. I know this isn't easy for you...
Akito: Why are you apologizing? I chose to take this on.
Akito: If anything, I should be the one apologizing for freaking out. I know he's your partner...
Ishihara: Shinonome...
Akito: Lemme give it another try... I'll get it right this time for su—
???: *Howl* Woof! Woof!
Akito: (Huh? That wasn't Max or either of our other dogs. Was someone else's nearby...?)
???: Hm? Shinonome, is that you?
Akito: Wait, huh...?!
Rui: What are the odds of us bumping into each other here?
Honami: Kamishiro...!
Rui: Ah, Mochizuki, Hanasato. How have you both been? Good, I hope.
Minori: Yes, and it's very nice to see you again!
Ishihara: Sorry, this is...?
Akito: Oh, he's a senior at my school. Not the best example, though.
Minori: Is this your dog, Kamishiro? It's so cute and fluffy and... Hang on a second...
Honami: It's making this sort of buzzing noise...
Akito: Don't tell me. It's...
Rui: Yes, a dog robot.
Rui: I happened to come across this old build while cleaning my room. So, I decided to give it some upgrades and take it out for a walk to see if it still works.
Minori: Wh-What...?! You made this dog yourself, Kamishiro?!
Honami: Th-That's astounding...
Akito: What can't you make at this point...?
Robo-Dog: Woof!
Akito: (Whoa, it even barks like a real dog...)
Rui: By the way, can I ask what you were all doing just now...?
Akito: Oh, we were practicing for a disc dog competition...
Rui: Disc dog...?
Ishihara: Yes. He's taking my place due to an injury that I've sustained.
Rui: Oh, I see. Still, are you sure about this...?
Akito: Huh...?
Rui: Based on your behavior, I get the feeling that you're having quite a lot of trouble.
Rui: In particular, when it comes to interacting with a dog.
Akito: What? How did you...?
Rui: Hehe. I'd rather you didn't underestimate a director's intuition.
Akito: Urgh...
Akito: But you're right. It hasn't been going all that well...
Rui: I see... You have no problem throwing the disc, but have trouble taking it back from the dog.
Akito: Yes. That's why I need to get back to practicing...
Rui: Hmm...
Rui: (I could conceivably take his place in this competition...)
Rui: (But Shinonome seems to be doing his best to work with Max...)
Rui: (So, I should try giving him whatever support I can.)
Rui: I understand why you feel so pressured since the competition is tomorrow, but I feel that you first need to get used to being with a dog before practicing with the disc...
Rui: I fear that you'll never succeed while this phobia of yours goes unresolved.
Akito: But...
Rui: So, let's see... You could start by petting or playing with him.
Akito: Playing with him?
Akito: Would that really work?
Minori: I agree with him!
Honami: Me too... I feel that you'll be able to take the disc from him without any issues if you take things slowly one step at a time.
Akito: ... Yeah, I guess that makes sense...
Akito: But I'm still not sure about petting him...
Honami: Oh, in that case, why don't I start by petting him while you watch...?
Honami: He's only just met me. So, seeing me pet him should in theory make things a little easier for you.
Ishihara: She has a point...
Akito: Then, if you don't mind...
Honami: Of course.
Honami: First, introduce yourself by letting him smell the back of your hand. Like this...
Akito: Introduce myself?
Honami: Yes. Dogs are no different from us humans. We don't like being touched by strangers.
Honami: Which is why it's important to give dogs a chance to first learn your scent. That's the initial step towards forming a bond with them.
Akito: I see...
Honami: When you go to pet him, try starting by gently scratching his jaw. I'd avoid his head or bottom since many dogs don't like being touched there immediately.
Akito: ...
Honami: That's about it. How do you feel, Shinonome...?
Akito: Alright, I'll give it a try...
Akito: (First, present the back of your hand...)
Max: *Sniff*
Akito: ...!
Minori: Oh no...!
Rui: This is going to be far more difficult than I realized...
Akito: (Argh! I can't stop my body from pulling away whenever a dog comes near...)
Akito: (Is it impossible for me to even introduce myself to him...?)
Rui: May I ask how long you've been afraid of dogs, Shinonome?
Akito: Huh...?
Rui: Understanding the root cause of your phobia may help us find the right solution. Would you mind telling us what happened exactly?
Akito: But...
Akito: Alright, I'll tell you guys...
Akito: It happened one day when I was still in preschool. I went to play at the park with my family and...
